FBIS4-31526 "dreeu112_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-112 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Krajina Serbs `Continue To Starve' Bihac Krajina Serbs `Continue To Starve' Bihac AU1006121694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 10 Jun 94 AU1006121694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] The chetniks continue to starve the population of the Bihac area by not allowing the passage of 20 convoys with humanitarian aid. Here is a report by our correspondent Fahrudin Bekcic: [Begin Bekcic recording] Because of [words indistinct] aggressor's and Abdic's blockade of a part of the Velika Kladusa commune, the Bihac district has been in total humanitarian isolation since 17 May. The humanitarian aid convoys [word indistinct] Bosnia-Herzegovina were halted at the Turanj checkpoint near Karlovac, which is in Serbian hands. They would not allow passage to 20 convoys for Bihac, Cazin, Bosanska Krupa, and (?Buzim), even though this are convoys of the international humanitarian organizations. At the same time the humanitarian aid is passing for [words indistinct] Velika Kladusa without any problems. [passage omitted] Instead of 15 kg, the residents of this region have been receiving only 7 kg of food per month. Now the situation is deteriorating rapidly. Food and other essentials are in short supply for nearly 300,000 residents of the Bihac district. [passage omitted] [end recording]
